SENATE BILL 2081
By Watson
HOUSE BILL 1956
By Alexander
AN ACT to amend Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 8;
Title 56; Title 63; Title 68 and Title 71, relative to
step therapy.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 56-7-3501(1), is amended by
deleting "stage 4 advanced metastatic cancer, metastatic blood cancer, or treatment of such
cancers" and substituting "cancer or the treatment of cancer".
SECTION 2. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 56-7-3501, is amended by deleting
subdivision (10).
SECTION 3. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 56-7-3502(h)(1), is amended by
deleting the subdivision and substituting:
(1) Notwithstanding this section, and except as provided in subdivision (h)(3), a
health benefit plan that provides coverage for cancer and associated conditions shall not
require use of a step therapy protocol before the health benefit plan provides coverage
of an approved prescription drug to an enrollee who has received a diagnosis of cancer.
SECTION 4. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 56-7-3502(h)(2), is amended by
deleting "stage 4 advanced metastatic cancer or metastatic blood".
SECTION 5. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 56-7-3502(h)(5), is amended by
deleting "stage 4 advanced metastatic cancer and metastatic blood".
SECTION 6. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 56-7-3502(h)(6), is amended by
deleting "stage 4 advanced metastatic cancer or metastatic blood" in subdivision (B) and (C).
